sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM category_products
WHERE category_id = 'specific_category_id';

SELECT COUNT(user_id)
FROM category_access
WHERE category_id = 'Category1';

SELECT c.name
FROM categories c
WHERE c.category_id IN (
  SELECT cp.category_id
  FROM category_products cp
) AND c.published = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Frequent visitors refer to users who access the category more often. ; 
- Contact details include user names and email addresses. ; 
- The top trio means the three users with the highest access counts.

- 'items' refers to 'products';
- 'feedback' implies 'reviews';
- 'comments' means 'total_reviews';
- 'satisfaction score' refers to 'average_rating'.

- "gardeners" refers to the users who have access to the categories;
- "blooming nurseries" are the categories that are "live" in their publication status;
- "vibrant array of more than three blossoms" means categories with more than three products.

sql:
SELECT meta_title, meta_keywords, meta_description, canonical_url 
FROM seo_metadata 
WHERE category_id = 'your_category_id';

SELECT categories.category_id, users.user_name
FROM categories
JOIN users ON categories.created_by = users.user_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM categories 
WHERE created_by = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE user_name = 'John Doe');

SELECT AVG(page_views) AS AveragePageViews 
FROM category_performance 
WHERE category_id = 'specified_category_id';

SELECT category_id, SUM(page_views) AS total_views
FROM category_performance
GROUP BY category_id;
